(597, 42, 157, '<p><strong>Which one of the following professionals does NOT have a privileged information status with their client? </strong></p>', 'Medical doctors.', 'Certified public accountants.', 'Attorneys.', 'Religious ministers.', '', '2', '', '', 'Active', 'Incorrect. A medical doctor has the privilege under our laws so that they may treat patients psychologically as well as physically.', 'Correct. For the most part, CPAs cannot disclose confidential information, but they are not protected by law or given privileged information status exempting them from being required to do so.', 'Incorrect. In order to be an advocate for their client, attorneys have the right to not disclose communications with them.', 'Incorrect. In order to minister adequately and appropriately to members or parishioners, ministers of religious orders have privilege.', ''),
(598, 42, 157, '<p><strong>Which kind of <em>working papers </em>may a client request, and have a right to receive from its auditor?</strong></p>', 'Analyses and comments on management’s strengths and weaknesses.', 'Papers that contain support for a client’s journal entries and that the client does not have a copy of.', 'Auditor’s comments and conclusions concerning materiality.', 'Both a & c.', '', '2', '', '', 'Active', 'Incorrect. Analyses of and comments on management’s strengths and weaknesses are made to determine future work and do not have to be given to the client.', 'Correct. Sole support for any part of the financial statements is the basis for the client having a right to the auditor’s working papers.', 'Incorrect. Auditor’s comments and conclusions concerning materiality are made to determine future work and do not have to be given to the client.', 'Incorrect. Analyses of and comments on management’s strengths and weaknesses are made to determine future work and do not have to be given to the client. Auditor’s comments and conclusions concerning materiality are made to determine future work and do not have to be given to the client.', ''),
(599, 42, 157, '<p><strong>Which one of the following groups does NOT require disclosure of commissions or anticipated commissions?</strong></p>', 'The AICPA Ethics Division.', 'Those members in public practice who do not perform an audit or review, examination of prospective statements, or compilation when independent.', 'The client.', 'The State Board of the state in which the professional is practicing in.', '', '1', '', '', 'Active', 'Correct. No disclosure is required to the AICPA.', 'Incorrect.  A member in public practice who do not perform an audit or review, examination of prospective statements, or compilation when independent is required and is not an exception to the rules.', 'Incorrect.  A professional is always required to disclose to their client.', 'Incorrect. A professional is not required to disclose commissions or anticipated commissions to the Board of the State in which they practice.', ''),
(600, 42, 158, '<p><strong>The attest engagement team includes all of the following, EXCEPT:</strong></p>', 'The proprietor who participates in the acceptance or performance of the attest engagement.', 'The partners who participate in the acceptance or performance of the attest engagement.', 'Full- or part-time professional staff in another office of the same firm in the same state who did not participate in the attest engagement.', 'The shareholders who participate in the acceptance or performance of the attest engagement.', '', '3', '', '', 'Active', 'Incorrect. The proprietor has to remain independent in order to participate in the performance of the attest engagement.', 'Incorrect. The partners have to remain independent in order to participate in the performance of the attest engagement.', 'Correct. These staff members would not be required to be independent since they had nothing to do with the attest engagement and were not in the same office.', 'Incorrect. The shareholders have to remain independent in order to participate in the performance of the attest engagement.', ''),
(601, 42, 158, '<p><strong>Upon determining that a supervisor&rsquo;s recommendation for treatment of financial information could result in a material misstatement, the first step in the CPA&rsquo;s ethical obligation is to:</strong></p>', 'Quit to avoid ethical violations.', 'Communicate concerns to the external accountant and all regulatory agencies that may be involved.', 'Report the disagreement to the supervisor’s supervisor.', 'Do sufficient research and consultation to determine if the supervisor is correct.', '', '4', '', '', 'Active', 'Incorrect. This is the third step.', 'Incorrect. This is the fourth step.', 'Incorrect. This is the second step.', 'Correct. Determining if the supervisor is correct is the first step of a CPA’s ethical obligation in a matter of disagreement with a supervisor.', ''),
(602, 42, 158, '<p><strong>When is a contingent fee or commission deemed to be received?</strong></p>', 'When money for services is first received.', 'When services have been performed and the fee or commission is determined.', 'When a client agrees to have a member perform a service for the client.', 'When an initial sales contact is made with a client.', '', '2', '', '', 'Active', 'Incorrect. The receipt of money for the first time is not the first time the fee could be deemed received.', 'Correct. When the fee or commission can be determined is the time it is deemed received.', 'Incorrect. This is not the best time to consider a fee to be received.', 'Incorrect. A fee has not yet been earned.', ''),
(603, 42, 158, '<p><strong>Which of the following statements is FALSE? &nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>When an Attest Function CPA performs &ldquo;Other Services&rdquo; the client must be in a position to have an informed judgment on the results of the other services and understand its responsibility to:</strong></p>', 'Designate a staff member to be responsible for overseeing the services being provided.', 'Evaluate the adequacy of the services performed and any findings that result.', 'Make management decisions, including accepting responsibility for the results of the other services.', 'Establish and maintain internal controls, including monitoring ongoing activities.', '', '1', '', '', 'Active', 'Correct. The company must designate a Management-level individual to be responsible for overseeing the services being provided, not a staff person.', 'Incorrect. The client is responsible for evaluating the adequacy of the services performed and any findings that result.', 'Incorrect. The client is responsible for making management decisions, including accepting responsibility for the results of the other services.', 'Incorrect. The client is responsible for establishing and maintaining internal controls, including monitoring ongoing activities.', ''),
(604, 42, 158, '<p><strong>Which of the following new loans to be obtained from a financial institution client where independence is required is NOT an &ldquo;Other Permitted Loan&rdquo;?</strong></p>', 'Automobile loans and leases collateralized by the automobile.', 'Loans fully collateralized by the cash surrender value of an insurance policy.', 'Loans partially collateralized by cash deposits at the same financial institution.', 'Credit cards where the aggregate outstanding balance on the current statement is reduced to $5,000 or less by the payment due date.', '', '3', '', '', 'Active', 'Incorrect. Collateralized automobile loans are permitted.', 'Incorrect. Fully collateralized loans by an insurance policy are permitted.', 'Correct. Partially collateralized loans are not permitted, no matter the collateral.', 'Incorrect. Credit cards of $5,000 or less are permitted.', ''),
(605, 43, 151, '<p><strong>Which of the following is a synonym for &ldquo;ethics&rdquo;?</strong></p>', 'Moral practice.', 'Social values.', 'Decency.', 'All of the above.', '', '4', '', '', 'Active', 'Incorrect.  Moral practice is not the best answer.', 'Incorrect. Social values are not the best answer.', 'Incorrect. Decency is not the best answer.', 'Correct. All of the above answers are synonyms for “ethics.”', ''),
(606, 43, 151, '<p><strong>Which of the following words is NOT a synonym of &ldquo;ethical&rdquo;?</strong></p>', 'Honest', 'Conscientious', 'Moral', 'Humane', '', '3', '', '', 'Active', 'Incorrect. Honest is being ethical.', 'Incorrect. Being Conscientious is being ethical.', 'Correct. Moral may or may not be ethical. The Mafia has their “moral code” which society does not consider ethical.', 'Incorrect. Being Humane is being ethical.', ''),
(607, 43, 151, '<p><strong>The sections of the Code of Ethics consist of _________ and _________:</strong></p>', 'Principles and Standards.', 'Rules and Standards.', 'Principles and Rules.', 'Rules, Principles, and Standards.', '', '3', '', '', 'Active', 'Incorrect.  Standards are not one of the sections.', 'Incorrect.  Principles must be one of the sections.', 'Correct. The two sections are Principles and Rules.', 'Incorrect. Standards are a subset of the Rules, not one of the sections.', ''),
(608, 43, 151, '<p><strong>Which of the following is NOT considered a Covered Member?</strong></p>', 'An individual on the attest engagement team.', 'A Partner in an office in the same state.', 'An individual in a position to influence the attest engagement.', 'The firm, including the firm''s employee benefit plans.', '', '2', '', '', 'Active', 'Incorrect. An individual on the attest engagement team is a Covered Member.', 'Correct. A Partner in an office in the same state is not necessarily a covered member.  Other attributes must be present.', 'Incorrect. An individual in a position to influence the attest engagement is a Covered Member.', 'Incorrect. The firm, including the firm''s employee benefit plans, is a Covered Member.', ''),
(609, 43, 151, '<p><strong>A member should consult, in addition to the Code of Professional Ethics, if applicable, the ethical standards of:</strong></p>', 'The state society to which the member belongs.', 'The appropriate state board of accountancy.', 'The AICPA ethics division.', 'All of the above.', '', '4', '', '', 'Active', 'Incorrect. The state society to which the member belongs is not the best answer.', 'Incorrect. The appropriate state board of accountancy is not the best answer.', 'Incorrect. The AICPA ethics division is not the best answer.', 'Correct. All of the above answers are appropriate.', ''),
(610, 43, 152, '<p><strong>Which one of the following definitions is NOT correct?</strong></p>', 'Council: the Council of the AICPA.', 'Member: a member, associate member, or international associate of the AICPA.', 'Professional services: all services performed by a member while performing public accounting services.', 'Institute: the American Institute of Certified Public Accountants.', '', '3', '', '', 'Active', 'Incorrect.  Council is properly defined as “The Council of the AICPA.” The Council is the governing body of the AICPA and is comprised of approximately 265 members and representatives from every state and U.S. Territory. Council meets twice a year, in May and October, and Regional Council meetings are held every year in March.', 'Incorrect.  Member is properly defined as “A member, associate member, or international associate of the AICPA.”', 'Correct. Professional services include all services performed by a member while holding out as a CPA, not just while performing public accounting services.', 'Incorrect. Institute is properly defined as “The American Institute of Certified Public Accountants.”', ''),
(611, 43, 152, '<p><strong>Which of the following items completes the following sentence?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Independence in Fact:</strong></p>', 'involves impartiality.', 'indicates that the member has abstained from relationships that appear to prevent objectivity.', 'is a state of mind.', 'involves freedom from conflicts of interest.', '', '3', '', '', 'Active', 'Incorrect. Impartiality is connected with objectivity.', 'Incorrect. Independence in appearance, not fact, involves actions such as abstaining from relationships.', 'Correct. Independence is attitudinal - a state of mind. Independence in appearance involves actions.', 'Incorrect. Objectivity involves actions such as freedom from conflicts of interest.', ''),
(612, 43, 152, '<p><strong>The unique characteristics of the accounting profession that set it apart from the rest of society is its acceptance of its responsibility to:</strong></p>', 'Its clients.', 'The government and its agencies.', 'The public.', 'Investors.', '', '3', '', '', 'Active', 'Incorrect. A profession is responsible to its clients, but this is not the best answer.', 'Incorrect. A profession is responsible to certain government agencies at times, but this is not the best answer.', 'Correct.  A profession is responsible to its public, which is unique.', 'Incorrect. A profession is responsible to investors sometimes, but this is not the best answer.', ''),
(613, 43, 152, '<p><strong>Which of the following statements is NOT correct? </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>A Key position is a position in which an individual: </strong></p>', 'Has primary responsibility for significant accounting functions that support material components of the financial statements.', 'Has responsibility for the sales force.', 'Has primary responsibility for the preparation of the financial statements.', 'Has the ability to exercise influence over the contents of the financial statements, including when the individual is a member of the board of directors.', '', '2', '', '', 'Active', 'Incorrect.  Having primary responsibility for significant accounting functions that support material components of the financial statements gives the possibility of adversely affecting the financial statements and they are therefore in a key position.', 'Correct. Having responsibility for the sales force does NOT allow the person to impact adversely the financial statements.', 'Incorrect.  Primary responsibility for the preparation of the financial statements allows the individual to adversely impact the financial statements and makes them in a key position.', 'Incorrect. The ability to exercise influence over the contents of the financial statements in any capacity is a key position.', ''),
