(6, '15 Tips on Becoming a Great Consultant', '<p>This&nbsp;course is a simple and useful guide designed for financial professionals, including&nbsp;but not limited to, CPAs, accountants, financial professionals, and IT professionals. The course provides an overview of the non-technical issues that are important to any consultant with practical considerations and ideas that can be used for any consulting project. The course is designed to assist with developing and/or refining consulting skills, consisting of&nbsp;5 chapters,&nbsp;each one presents three tips to improve one&rsquo;s consulting abilities, with the goal of an increase in overall competence as a consultant.</p>', '15_tips_on_becoming_a_great_consultant_pencilcup-sm3.jpg', 10.00, 0.00, 'QAS Self Study', 'None', 'Basic', 1.50, 70.00, 'None', 12, '57', '2016-06-14', '#ffd6d6', 'active', 'Text', '6', '15_tips_on_becoming_a_great_consultant_toc.pdf', '', 'Communications'),
(7, 'A Guide to Expanding Your Practice: Adding Financial Planning', '<p>This is a basic course for CPAs and PAs that covers the necessary processes when a CPA firm adds the service of Financial Planning for their clients.&nbsp; It encompasses the areas of expertise needed by the CPA to be a professional Financial Planner. Coverage of the areas of the financial plan is provided through basic discussion of the concepts, theories, and definitions involved in the financial planning process. Guidelines are provided for the CPA&#39;s implementation of the financial planning process from the data gathering through the implementation of the financial plan to the periodic reviews.&nbsp;</p>', 'a_guide_to_expanding_your_practice:_adding_financial_planning_wallst_bg_color2.jpg', 36.00, 0.00, 'QAS Self Study', 'None', 'Basic', 4.00, 70.00, 'None', 12, '57', '2016-06-16', '#fffbd3', 'active', 'Text', '6', 'a_guide_to_expanding_your_practice:_adding_financial_planning_overview_page_final_.pdf', '', 'Finance'),
(8, 'Accountants Wanted: A Brief Overview of the Profession', '<p>This&nbsp;interactive self-study course&nbsp;provides a review of the causes and effects of the demand for accountants. &nbsp;&nbsp;Due, in part, to the rise in entrepreneurs, new businesses, ever-changing financial laws and regulations, and an increase in the inspection of company finances, the need for accountants and auditors is exponential. &nbsp;This course was designed for accountants seeking to develop a greater understanding as to the direction in which the accounting profession is going. &nbsp;The course delves into the causes and effects of the increased demand for accounting professionals, what is required to keep up with the ever-changing field and demands, as well as the information required in order to have the ability to compete with other organizations to retain the most qualified accountants. &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>', 'accountants_wanted:_a_brief_overview_of_the_profession_calculator_sm.png', 14.00, 0.00, 'QAS Self Study', 'None', 'Overview', 1.00, 70.00, 'None', 12, '23', '2016-08-01', '#fbd6c6', 'active', 'Text', '6', 'accountants_wanted:_a_brief_overview_of_the_profession_overview_page_.pdf', '', 'Business Management & Organization'),
(9, 'Accounting for Liabilities', '<p>This interactive self-study course is designed to provide&nbsp;financial professionals, including but not limited to CPAs and PAs, an overview of the accounting complexities related to estimated liabilities and contingent liabilities.&nbsp; The course also explains customer loyalty programs, warranties, and asset retirement obligations.&nbsp; Additionally, the course details GAAP-based recognition and disclosure methods.&nbsp;</p>', 'accounting_for_liabilities_bills_sm.jpg', 14.00, 0.00, 'QAS Self Study', 'None', 'Basic', 1.50, 70.00, 'None', 12, '27', '2016-09-14', '#cbd5ff', 'active', 'Text', '6', 'accounting_for_liabilities_overview_page_.pdf', '', 'Accounting'),
(10, 'An Effective Accounts Payable Policy & Procedures Manual', '<p>This course is an&nbsp;overview&nbsp;designed to provide financial professionals, including but not limited to CPAs, PAs, Auditors, Controllers, and Managers interested in creating an Effective Accounts Payable Policy and Procedures manual.&nbsp; Effective policies and procedures in the Accounts Payable function is critical for any organization wishing to reduce or eliminate duplicate payments, prevent and detect fraud, be cost effective and compliant with all regulatory issues affecting the payment function. The first step in that battle is having a current, detailed policy and procedures manual. &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This course presents information the professional can use to create an effective manual, that not only documents the organizations policies and procedures, can be used as a reference and training guide. Industry expert Mary Schaeffer shows auditors, controllers, and managers how to create such a manual when none exists. She also includes an outline for a sample policy as well as a checklist they can use to determine if their current policy is best practice or something less.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'an_effective_accounts_payable_policy_&_procedures_manual_checksign.jpg', 18.00, 0.00, 'QAS Self Study', 'None', 'Overview', 2.00, 70.00, 'None', 12, '13', '2016-08-12', '#dee1ff', 'active', 'Text', '6', 'an_effective_accounts_payable_policy_&_procedures_manual_overview_page_final.pdf', '', 'Accounting'),
(11, 'An Overview of Fraud in the Workplace', '<p>This&nbsp;course is an overview of employee fraud in the workplace and how to prevent and handle it if it occurs. &nbsp; The course&nbsp;is intended for all financial professionals, including but not limited to CPAs, PAs, CFEs, CFPs, CEOs, and CFOs.&nbsp; The course begins with a discussion about the background of employee fraud.&nbsp; It then addresses some of the most common types of asset misappropriation, and the methods used to detect and prevent fraud.</p>', 'an_overview_of_fraud_in_the_workplace_suitcase_sm.jpg', 14.00, 0.00, 'QAS Self Study', 'None', 'Overview', 1.50, 70.00, 'None', 12, '27', '2016-06-15', '#a9d9e0', 'active', 'Text', '6', 'an_overview_of_fraud_in_the_workplace_overview_page_final.pdf', '', 'Auditing'),
(12, 'Asset Valuation Using Discounted Cash Flows', '<p>This is a basic course on asset valuation using discounted cash flows, intended to provide accounting and auditing professionals with an overview of the Discounted Cash-Flow (DCF) Method of valuation. The DCF method requires that an estimated cash-flow and a risk-adjusted discount rate be determined.&nbsp; The&nbsp;course summarizes commonly-used cash-flow proxies and discount rate estimation tools.</p>', 'asset_valuation_using_discounted_cash_flows_calendar.jpg', 18.00, 0.00, 'QAS Self Study', 'None', 'Overview', 1.50, 70.00, 'None', 12, '27', '2016-06-15', '#f1f7c3', 'active', 'Text', '6', 'asset_valuation_using_discounted_cash_flows_overview_final.pdf', '', 'Accounting'),
(13, 'Electronic Payments: How Savvy Companies Pay their Bills', '<p>This course provides an overview of the ACH payment process. &nbsp;The course&nbsp;is&nbsp;designed for all financial professionals to provide them with an overview of the ACH process.&nbsp; Almost three-quarters of all companies now make at least a few payments electronically using the ACH. Those numbers, along with the size of those programs will only grow as organizations recognize the cost-savings and efficiencies associated with an ACH payment program.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The&nbsp;course presents basic information the professional can use to properly set up and grow and ACH payment program.&nbsp; Industry expert Mary Schaeffer shows auditors, controllers, and managers exactly how to do this. She also alerts readers to the growing threat of fraud in this arena, offering advice for everyone &ndash; whether or not they are currently making electronic payments. &ldquo;Everyone who does not take the proper precautions are at risk,&rdquo; she warns.&nbsp;</p>', 'electronic_payments:_how_savvy_companies_pay_their_bills_faculty-w.png', 18.00, 0.00, 'QAS Self Study', 'None', 'Overview', 2.00, 70.00, 'None', 12, '13', '2016-08-15', '#c7b3df', 'pending', 'Text', '6', 'electronic_payments:_how_savvy_companies_pay_their_bills_toc_final.pdf', '', 'Accounting'),
(14, 'Best Practices for Accounts Payable', '<p>Best practices for the accounts payable function are critical for those organizations concerned about their profitability. &nbsp;For poor practices result in excess cost, duplicate payments, increased processing expenses, fraud and frayed vendor relationships. And, of course there is the growing issue of regulatory compliance as the Feds and states look for their fair share. &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This course presents information the professional can use to identify best practice problems as well as regulatory concerns. &nbsp;Industry expert Mary S. Schaeffer explains the issues related to the accounts payable function to auditors, controllers, and managers. She then reveals the best practices for a myriad of these issues as well as identifying almost best practices for those cases where it is not possible to use the best practice and the worst practices which are likely to cause trouble. &nbsp;</p>', 'best_practices_for_accounts_payable_coins.jpg', 116.00, 0.00, 'QAS Self Study', 'None', 'Basic', 13.00, 70.00, 'None', 12, '13', '2016-09-19', '#e7e3ff', 'active', 'Text', '6', 'best_practices_for_accounts_payable_overview_page_final.pdf', '', 'Accounting'),
(15, 'Best Practices for Invoice Handling', '<p>This course is a short and to-the-point overview of invoice handling.&nbsp; It is intended for financial professionals eager understand the best practices for the invoice handling function and how critical it is for those organizations concerned about their profitability.&nbsp; The course explains how poor practices in invoice handling result in excess cost, duplicate payments, increased processing expenses, fraud and frayed vendor relationships. This course presents information the professional can use to identify best practice problems. Industry expert Mary S. Schaeffer explains the invoice issues. She then reveals the best practices for a myriad of these problems as well as identifying almost best practices for those cases where it is not possible to use the best practice and the worst practices which are likely to cause trouble. &nbsp;</p>', 'best_practices_for_invoice_handling_reading-papers.jpg', 10.00, 0.00, 'QAS Self Study', 'None', 'Overview', 1.00, 70.00, 'None', 12, '13', '2016-08-15', '#e1df9b', 'active', 'Text', '6', 'best_practices_for_invoice_handling_overview_final.pdf', '', 'Accounting'),
(16, 'Derivatives and Hedging', '<p>This course is designed to provide a clear and relevant overview of derivatives and hedging, beneficial to any financial professional seeking to gain knowledge and understanding about today&rsquo;s financial markets.&nbsp; A Derivative is a financial product that derives its value based on an underlying asset, liability, or other variable (such as an interest rate, foreign currency, or commodity price). Derivatives have become very popular tools for &ldquo;hedging&rdquo; (i.e. reducing) financial risk; they have also become an increasingly standard item on big companies&#39; balance sheets. Yet understanding how they work, what they are used for, and how they can affect the bottom line of a business has proven to be a significant challenge for the accounting and auditing industries.</p>', 'derivatives_and_hedging_bag-of-money.jpg', 54.00, 0.00, 'QAS Self Study', 'None', 'Overview', 6.00, 70.00, 'None', 12, '38', '2016-07-31', '#95dfe1', 'active', 'Text', '6', 'derivatives_and_hedging_overview_final.pdf', '', 'Finance'),
(17, 'Maintaining Your Business During a Disaster', '<p>This is a basic course designed to introduce financial professionals to the process of developing, communicating and testing a disaster recovery plan to avoid potential pitfalls and ensure the continuation of critical business operations in the case of an unforeseeable event.&nbsp; We will begin by taking a look at a mock scenario of a company which experiences a flood during the normal course of a day.&nbsp; This company does not have a disaster plan in place and as a result, experiences a huge loss both financially and emotionally.</p>', 'maintaining_your_business_during_a_disaster_faculty-w.png', 18.00, 0.00, 'QAS Self Study', 'None', 'Basic', 2.00, 70.00, 'None', 12, '23', '2016-08-01', '#c7b3df', 'pending', 'Text', '6', 'maintaining_your_business_during_a_disaster_overview_final.pdf', '', 'Business Management & Organization'),
(18, '20 Tips for becoming management expert', '<p>This&nbsp;course is a simple and useful guide designed for management professionals, including&nbsp;but not limited to, CPAs, accountants, management professionals, and IT professionals. The course provides an overview of the non-technical issues that are important to any consultant with practical considerations and ideas that can be used for any consulting project. The course is designed to assist with developing and/or refining consulting skills, consisting of&nbsp;5 chapters,&nbsp;each one presents three tips to improve one&rsquo;s consulting abilities, with the goal of an increase in overall competence as a expert.</p>', '20_tips_for_becoming_management_expert_hydrangeas.jpg', 35.00, 5.00, 'Sef study', 'none', 'intermediate', 4.00, 75.00, 'none', 3, '81', '2016-09-23', '#55db8b', 'deleted', 'Text', '1', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tvoqT_yhfnQ', 'management'),
