(45, 'What’s New and Improved for QuickBooks Desktop 2016', '<p>In this informative webcast presented by Quickbooks Expert, Laura Madeira, &nbsp;she thoroughly explains and demonstrates the 2016 features of Quickbooks. &nbsp;Discover features that are unique to your QuickBooks Accountant software, as well those used by your clients with QuickBooks Pro, Premier, and Enterprise. This course is designed for any professional that utilizes Quickbooks&nbsp;or has clients that use Quickbooks. &nbsp;Ms. Madeira takes the guess-work out of working with new features. &nbsp;</p>', 'what’s_new_and_improved_for_quickbooks_desktop_2016_faculty-w.png', 10.00, 0.00, 'QAS Self Study On-Demand Webcast', 'None', 'Basic', 1.00, 70.00, 'None', 12, '32', '2016-08-15', '#c7b3df', 'active', 'Text', '6', 'what’s_new_and_improved_for_quickbooks_desktop_2016_quickbooks_overview.pdf', '', 'Computer Science'),
(46, 'Sales and Use Tax Nexus', '<p>Tax&nbsp;</p>', 'sales_and_use_tax_faculty-m.png', 36.00, 0.00, 'QAS Self Study', 'None', 'Basic', 3.00, 70.00, 'None', 12, '39', '2016-11-02', '#c7b3df', 'pending', 'Text', '6', '', '', 'Taxes'),
(47, 'Excel Enlightenment: Charts', '<p>In this informative on-demand webcast, our faculty member and Excel expert David Ringstrom, CPA, demonstrates a variety of techniques and tricks that enable you to create and automate your Excel charts. He explains several helpful features in Excel, including Sparkline feature, PivotCharts, Recommended Charts feature, and more. In addition, he shows you how to use templates to avoid repetitive formatting tasks, how to create self-updating charts and chart titles, and how to use clip art to liven up your charts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>David&rsquo;s materials cover Excel 2016, 2013, 2010, and 2007. Depending on the topic, he demonstrates techniques in Excel 2010, 2013, or 2016 while noting differences in other versions of Excel when warranted. David&rsquo;s detailed handouts, with numbered steps, serve as reference material you can utilize going forward. He also provides an Excel workbook that includes most of the examples he uses to demonstrate techniques during the presentation.</p>', 'excel_enlightenment:_charts_faculty-m.png', 18.00, 0.00, 'QAS Self Study', 'None', 'Basic', 2.00, 70.00, 'None', 12, '9', '2016-08-26', '#c7b3df', 'pending', 'Text', '6', '', '', 'Computer Science'),
(48, 'Ethics Principles and Conduct for California CPAs', '<p>This Ethics course satisfies the<strong> Four-hour </strong>requirement for all licensees in the state of California. &nbsp;The course introduces and explains the ethical standards for the CPA, whether employed in public or private accounting. &nbsp;Applications of these are discussed in a professional context. &nbsp;The California Accountancy Act and the California Board of Accountancy Rules and Regulations are discussed. &nbsp;Additionally, the concepts of integrity and objectivity are explained. &nbsp;When broad guidelines are used, interpretations are necessary in many cases due to the fact that guidelines are non-specific.&nbsp; Applications of these are discussed in a professional context. &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dr. Austin explains the issues, developments, and problems addressed by recent AICPA, Independence Standards Board, and SEC Ethics pronouncements and updates.&nbsp; The issues discussed are based on the American Institute of Certified Public Accountants (AICPA) Code of Professional Conduct, which is the standard for all CPAs. &nbsp;The last unit compares the AICPA Code of Ethics with ethics for attorneys and internal auditors, and ends with a discussion of California and U.S. cases of significant ethical violations.&nbsp;</p>', 'ethics_principles_and_conduct_for_california_cpas_california_blank_f1f7c3.png', 36.00, 0.00, 'QAS Self Study', 'None', 'Basic', 4.00, 70.00, 'None', 12, '8', '2016-01-01', '#f1f7c3', 'active', 'Text', '6', 'ethics_principles_and_conduct_for_california_cpas_california_ethics_overview_final_.pdf', '', 'Ethics'),
(49, 'Ethics Principles and Conduct for Pennsylvania CPAs', '<p>This Ethics course satisfies the Four-hour Ethics requirement for all licensees in the state of Pennsylvania.&nbsp; The course introduces and explains the ethical standards for the CPA, whether employed in public or private accounting. Applications of these are discussed in a professional context.&nbsp; The concepts of integrity and objectivity are discussed.&nbsp; When broad guidelines are used, interpretations are necessary in many cases due to the fact that guidelines are non-specific.&nbsp; Applications of these are discussed in a professional context. &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dr. Austin further explains the issues, developments, and problems addressed by recent AICPA, Independence Standards Board, and SEC Ethics pronouncements and updates.&nbsp; The issues discussed are based on the American Institute of Certified Public Accountants (AICPA) Code of Professional Conduct, which is the standard for all CPAs.&nbsp; The last unit compares the AICPA Code of Ethics with ethics for attorneys and internal auditors, and provides examples of United States court cases regarding the unethical behavior of financial and accounting professionals.&nbsp;</p>', 'ethics_principles_and_conduct_for_pennsylvania_cpas_pennsylvania_blank_ffe8eb.png', 36.00, 0.00, 'QAS Self Study', 'None', 'Basic', 4.00, 70.00, 'None', 12, '8', '2016-01-01', '#ffe8eb', 'active', 'Text', '6', 'ethics_principles_and_conduct_for_pennsylvania_cpas_pa_ethics_overview.pdf', '', 'Ethics'),
(50, 'Excel Enlightenment: New 2016 Features', '<p>This is a basic Excel course in which you will learn about new features available in Excel 2016, from expert David Ringstrom, CPA. &nbsp;In this informative course, he demonstrates how to simplify chart-related tasks, how to convert .XLS workbooks to the .XLSX format, and how to create interactive maps from Excel data with the free Bing Maps app.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mr. Ringstrom explains how to use the Flash Fill feature, the Recommended PivotTables feature, the Charts feature, the Slicer feature, and the Quick Analysis feature, as well as how to overcome user interface annoyances by making simple adjustments. &nbsp;In addition, he discusses the new charts available in Excel 2016, including Box and Whisker charts, Treemap charts, and Sunburst charts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Once you understand how Excel 2016 differs from previous versions, you can avoid any pitfalls and frustrations you might encounter when working in this new version of Excel. &nbsp;Mr. Ringstrom covers Excel 2016, but he points out any differences in earlier versions of Excel.</p>', 'excel_enlightenment:_new_2016_features_faculty-m.png', 18.00, 0.00, 'QAS Self Study On-Demand Webcast', 'None', 'Basic', 2.00, 70.00, 'None', 12, '9', '2016-08-26', '#c7b3df', 'active', 'Text', '6', 'excel_enlightenment:_new_2016_features_excel_2016_features_overview.pdf', '', 'Computer Science');
