(163, 35, 'Chapter 1', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Define the &lsquo;historical cost&rsquo; method of accounting and calculate the current &lsquo;amortized cost&rsquo; of assets and liabilities accounted for under this method.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Define the &lsquo;fair value&rsquo; method of accounting for assets and liabilities and recognize accounting practices consistent with this method.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Recognize the differences between the &lsquo;historical cost&rsquo; and &lsquo;fair value&rsquo; methods of accounting.</li>\r\n</ul>', '#c7b3df', 'Active', 0),
(164, 35, 'Chapter 2', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Define &lsquo;fair value&rsquo; as outlined in ASC 820 <em>Fair Value Measurements and Disclosures</em>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Recognize accounting practices that are consistent with the fair value framework established in ASC 820.</li>\r\n</ul>', '#c7b3df', 'Active', 0),
(165, 35, 'Chapter 3', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Recognize valuation techniques that are consistent with the guidance of ASC 820.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Recognize the proper classification of valuation inputs into the levels of the fair value hierarchy.</li>\r\n</ul>', '#c7b3df', 'Active', 0),
(166, 35, 'Chapter 4', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Recognize accounting practices consistent with the fair value disclosure requirements outlined in ASC 820.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Recognize auditing practices consistent with the standards of fieldwork related to auditing fair value measurements and disclosures included in SAS No. 101.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Identify the roles that management and the auditor have in the fair value measurement process.</li>\r\n</ul>', '#c7b3df', 'Active', 0),
(167, 35, 'Chapter 5', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Recognize the proper application of the fair value option under ASC 825-10.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Identify assets &amp; liabilities that are eligible for the fair value option.</li>\r\n</ul>', '#c7b3df', 'Active', 0),
(168, 35, 'Chapter 6', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Recognize the principal arguments against fair value accounting&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Explain the limitations of applying the ASC 820 definition of fair value when markets are illiquid or inactive</li>\r\n</ul>', '#c7b3df', 'Active', 0),
(169, 46, 'Chapter 1', '<ul>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Recognize various forms of excise taxes.</li>\r\n	<li>Understand the Constitutional sources of power for assessing use taxes.</li>\r\n	<li>Understand different states&rsquo; taxing conventions on &ldquo;out-of-state&rdquo; transactions.</li>\r\n	<li>Understand various forms of contacts with a state which constitute a sufficient nexus with that state to allow the state to impose the burdens of a use tax.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>', '#c7b3df', 'Active', 0),
(170, 46, 'Chapter 2', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Understand the nexus requirements that are sufficient to establish presence in a state.</li>\r\n	<li>Identify key criteria for differentiating <em>de minimum</em> from sufficient physical presence.</li>\r\n	<li>Understand when rental of tangible personal property will constitute nexus.</li>\r\n	<li>Recognize nexus requirements for various forms of employment.</li>\r\n</ul>', '#c7b3df', 'Active', 0),
(171, 46, 'Chapter 3', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Recognize the varying criteria for determining nexus among the various states.</li>\r\n	<li>Understand requirements of &lsquo;more than the slightest presence&rsquo;.</li>\r\n	<li>Understand the scope of variety for different state&rsquo;s findings of the application of nexus.</li>\r\n	<li>Know the shortcomings of the &lsquo;More than Slightest Presence&rdquo; Rule.</li>\r\n	<li>Understand how a state can offer a &lsquo;safe harbor&rsquo; for trade show or seminar attendees.</li>\r\n</ul>', '#c7b3df', 'Active', 0),
(172, 46, 'Chapter 4', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Distinguish how return merchandise creates nexus.</li>\r\n	<li>Recognize the criteria for &ldquo;affiliate nexus.&quot;</li>\r\n	<li>Understand the tension of case law and statutory provisions governing the application of nexus requirements.</li>\r\n	<li>Analyze case-by-case activities in determining the creation of nexus.</li>\r\n</ul>', '#c7b3df', 'Active', 0),
(173, 46, 'Chapter 5', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Recognize a &lsquo;click through&rsquo; transaction.</li>\r\n	<li>Understand online activities that will trigger nexus considerations.</li>\r\n	<li>Recognize where there may be a rebuttable presumption of nexus.</li>\r\n</ul>', '#c7b3df', 'Active', 0),
(174, 46, 'Chapter 7', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Recognize when activities may lead to a nexus with a state.</li>\r\n	<li>Understand how to remedy outstanding back tax issues with multiple states.</li>\r\n	<li>Understand the nature and processes required by the Multistage Tax Commission Agreement.</li>\r\n	<li>Recognize&nbsp;the advantages of the MTC Agreement.</li>\r\n	<li>Explain the incentives in the creation of Marketplace Fairness Act.</li>\r\n</ul>', '#c7b3df', 'Active', 0),
(175, 46, 'Chapter 6', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Define state registration nexus requirements for purposes of doing business with the state.</li>\r\n	<li>Identify corporate undertakings that will create nexus for use, sales or franchise tax burdens.</li>\r\n	<li>Recognize typical issues with regard state reporting for nexus purposes.</li>\r\n	<li>Understand&nbsp;the care to be given to &ldquo;Nexus Questionnaires.&rdquo;</li>\r\n</ul>', '#c7b3df', 'Active', 0),
