(187, 49, 'Chapter 3', '<ul>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Differentiate Independence in Appearance and Fact.</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Analyze the rules of the Code of Ethics.</li>\r\n	<li>Apply the Standards of the rules of Ethics.</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Implement the GAAP rules.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Determine client confidentiality rules.</li>\r\n	<li>Summarize acts that are discreditable to the profession.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>', '#c7b3df', 'Active', 0),
(188, 49, 'Chapter 4', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Evaluate the impact of former employees and family members on Independence.</li>\r\n	<li>Examine the impact of Investment or Management Advisory Services on Independence.</li>\r\n	<li>Be familiar with possible conflicts of interest.</li>\r\n	<li>Understand the role of CPAs as employees.</li>\r\n</ul>', '#c7b3df', 'Active', 0),
(189, 50, 'Unit 1', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Identify the differences in Excel 2016 from previous versions in order to avoid the pitfalls and frustrations than can result from a lack of understanding.</li>\r\n</ul>', '#c7b3df', 'Active', 0),
(190, 50, 'Unit 2', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Recall how to use the Flash Fill feature, the Recommended Charts feature, the Slicer feature, and the Quick Analysis feature.</li>\r\n</ul>', '#c7b3df', 'Active', 0),
(191, 50, 'Unit 3', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Understand how to convert .XLS workbooks to the .XLSX format.</li>\r\n</ul>', '#c7b3df', 'Active', 0),
(192, 50, 'Unit 4', '<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Understand the new worksheet functions available in Excel 2016.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Identify the Flash Fill feature.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>&nbsp;Apply the Recommended PivotTables feature.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>', '#c7b3df', 'Active', 0),
(193, 50, 'Unit 5', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Identify the IFNA function available in Excel 2013 and later.</li>\r\n	<li>Determine how the Table feature allows you to transform filtering tasks.</li>\r\n	<li>Overcome user interface issues by making simple adjustments to Excel&rsquo;s options.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '#c7b3df', 'Active', 0),
(194, 50, 'Unit 6', '<ul>\r\n	<li>Formulate Box and Whisker charts in Excel 2016 to show data by quartiles and identify outliers.</li>\r\n	<li>Apply Excel 2016&rsquo;s Sunburst chart for displaying hierarchical data in a circular chart.</li>\r\n	<li>Evaluate Excel 2016&rsquo;s Treemap chart to visualize data based on relative size.</li>\r\n</ul>', '#c7b3df', 'Active', 0);
