(148, 16, 'Which of the following risk management practices would have most likely prevented the investment losses recognized by Fett Bank on 12/31/X2?', 'Monitoring the duration of their investments.', 'Prohibiting the purchase of below-investment-grade securities.', 'Matching interest-sensitive assets with interest-sensitive liabilities.', 'Purchasing a forward exchange forward contract.', '', '2', 'Active', NULL),
(149, 16, 'Which of the following contracts is most likely an example of an exchange-traded derivative?', 'Contract A is a customized instrument that allows its holder to lock in an exchange rate on the future purchase of foreign currency.', 'Contract B carries a significant amount of exposure to counterparty credit risk.', 'Contract C features standardized terms that were set defined by the Chicago Board of Trade.', 'Contract D represents a percentage of ownership in the issuing entity.', '', '3', 'Active', NULL),
(150, 16, 'Which of the following is an example of a forward contract?', 'Company A’s commitment to purchase 100 barrels of oil for delivery today at the current market price.', 'Company D’s first right of refusal to purchase a lot of real estate at a market rate.', 'Company C’s commitment to purchase 1,000,000 euros in 3 months at a specified exchange rate.', 'Company D’s right to sell 50,000 shares of Exxon Mobil common stock to a third party for $75 per share over the next 3 months.', '', '3', 'Active', NULL),
(151, 16, 'For questions 8-11, please refer to the facts below: <br />  Contract A is a 6 month long forward contract for 10,000 bushels of corn. The market price of corn on the contract execution date equals $3.00 per bushel.  The market price of corn on the delivery date specified in the contract equals $4.00 per bushel. <br />  Contract B is a 12 month short forward contract for 20,000 bushels of wheat. The market price of corn on the contract execution date equals $8.00 per bushel; however the delivery price included in the forward contract equals $7.00 per bushel.  <br /><br /> Which of the following best describes Grevious’ responsibilities under the terms of its corn forward contract?', 'Grievous is obligated to sell 10,000 bushels on the delivery date at the specified forward price.', 'Grievous is obligated to purchase 10,000 bushels on the delivery date at the specified forward price.', 'Grievous is obligated to sell 10,000 bushels on the delivery date at the current market price.', 'Grievous is obligated to purchase 10,000 bushels on the delivery date at the current market price.', '', '2', 'Active', NULL),
(152, 16, 'If the long forward contract results in a ($7,500) payoff loss for Grievous Inc., the forward price of corn included in the contract must have equaled:', '$3.00.', '$3.25.', '$3.75.', '$4.75.', '', '2', 'Active', NULL),
(153, 16, 'Under which of the following scenarios would Grievous earn a payoff profit on its short forward contract?', 'The market price of wheat increases to $10.00 per bushel.', 'The market price of wheat increases to $9.00 per bushel.', 'The market price of wheat declines to $7.00 per bushel.', 'The market price of wheat declines to $6.00 per bushel.', '', '4', 'Active', NULL),
(154, 16, 'The specific terms included in contract B were most likely determined by:', 'The counterparties involved.', 'A hedge fund manager.', 'A derivatives exchange.', 'A governmental agency.', '', '1', 'Active', NULL),
(155, 16, 'ABC Co. has entered into a short FX forward contract with XYZ Inc. in which they will lock in an exchange rate for the sale of Japanese yen (JPY) in 12 months. One US dollar currently buys 80 JPY. ABC Co. can earn a 4% return over the next 12 months on its JPY; however the company will incur a 6% opportunity cost by not selling the JPY today and reinvesting the proceeds. Under these conditions, the implied forward exchange rate (per 1 USD) on this contract should equal:', '78 JPY.', '78.4 JPY.', '81.6 JPY.', '82 JPY.', '', '3', 'Active', NULL),
(156, 16, 'Which of the following is an example of a company earning a profit as a result of arbitrage?', 'Company A purchases long and short 6 month oil forward contracts with the same forward price.', 'Company B purchases a security in the U.S. market for $100 and simultaneously sells that security in the European market for $105.', 'Company C purchases a share of stock for $75 and sells it for $90 three years later.', 'Company D issues floating rate debt and uses the proceeds to purchase a floating rate investment.', '', '2', 'Active', NULL),
(157, 16, 'For questions 14-16, please refer to the facts below: <br /> Sith Financial has entered into a 12 month forward rate agreement with one of their customers. Sith will receive a 3% annual interest rate under the agreement in exchange for an interest payment based on 12 month LIBOR. The notional principal on the trade equals $5,000,000.  <br /><br /> Sith’s customer most likely entered into the FRA in order to hedge:', 'Foreign exchange risk.', 'Credit risk.', 'Interest rate risk.', 'Liquidity risk.', '', '3', 'Active', NULL),
(158, 16, 'Which of the following best describes the role that the notional principal will serve in the forward rate agreement between Sith Financial and its customer?', 'The notional principal will be exchanged by the counterparties.', 'The notional principal will be held in a margin account.', 'The notional principal will serve no purpose under the terms of this FRA.', 'The notional principal will be used to calculate the cash flows paid and received.', '', '4', 'Active', NULL),
(159, 16, 'If 12 month LIBOR is observed as 4.25% in accordance with this FRA, the payoff will equal a ____________ to Sith Financial.', '$212,500 net loss.', '$62,500 net loss.', '$62,500 net gain.', '$212,500 net gain.', '', '2', 'Active', NULL),
(160, 16, 'Contract A is a forward agreement to purchase an asset at a specified price in 3 months. Contract B is a futures contract to purchase an asset at a specified price in 6 months. Which of the following statements is true regarding the credit risk associated with these contracts?', 'Contract A has more inherent credit risk than Contract B.', 'Contract B has more inherent credit risk than Contract A.', 'Contracts A & B have equal amounts of inherent credit risk.', 'Contracts A & B are generally considered credit risk free.', '', '1', 'Active', NULL),
(161, 16, 'Which of the following contracts is most likely an example of an exchange traded derivative?', 'Company A’s Eurobond futures contract.', 'Company B’s euro-denominated interest rate swap.', 'Company C’s euro-denominated loans receivable.', 'Company D’s euro forward contract.', '', '1', 'Active', NULL),
(162, 16, 'For questions 19 & 20, please refer to the facts below: <br /> The Maul Group has placed two oil futures orders. Under the first order, Maul will automatically sell 10,000 oil futures contracts if the market price falls below $70.  Under the second order, Maul will purchase 5,000 oil futures contracts at the current market price.  <br /> <br /> The Maul Group’s first futures order is an example of a:', 'Limit order.', 'Long order.', 'Stop order.', 'Market order.', '', '3', 'Active', NULL),
(163, 16, 'The Maul Group’s second futures order is an example of a:', 'Limit order.', 'Long order.', 'Stop order.', 'Market order.', '', '4', 'Active', NULL),
(164, 16, 'Which of the following represents a distinctive feature of the New York Mercantile Exchange (NYMEX)?', 'The terms for over-the-counter interest rate derivatives are standardized on the NYMEX.', 'The NYMEX simplifies the trading mechanics for coal futures contracts.', 'Trades on the NYMEX normally carry higher transaction costs than private deals.', 'Commodity derivatives traded on the NYMEX are considered highly illiquid.', '', '2', 'Active', NULL),
(165, 16, 'For questions 22-26 please refer to the facts below.   The following is an excerpt from a Sidious, Inc.’s futures margin account statement.  Sidious, Inc. opened this account on the morning of 6/1/X1.  <br /> <br /> The initial margin required on the Sidious margin account equals:', '$0.', '$3,000.', '$48,000.', '$50,000.', '', '4', 'Active', NULL),
