(188, 16, 'Under the terms of option A, Viceroy has the ________ to ________ the underlying stock at a price of $_______ per share.', 'Right; buy; $58.00.', 'Obligation; buy; $50.00.', 'Right; sell; $50.00.', 'Obligation; sell; $58.00.', '', '3', 'Active', NULL),
(189, 16, 'If the spot price of Option D’s underlying stock declined to $12.00 per share just prior to the expiration date, Viceroy would most likely:', 'Exercise the option and realize a $3 per share gain.', 'Allow the option to expire worthless.', 'Lock in their hedging gains using a forward contract.', 'Deliver the underlying stock for a $13 per share loss.', '', '2', 'Active', NULL),
(190, 16, 'For questions 47-49, please refer to the facts below.  <br />  In an effort to boost its financing activities, Tyranus, Corp. has issued several shares of common stock to investors in exchange for cash. Tyranus also sold put options to these investors that would allow them to sell the common stock back to Tyranus at $10 per share (in exchange for a $2 per share premium). <br /> <br /> Which of the following diagrams best represents the payoff profile of this option contract?', 'Graph A', 'Graph B', 'Graph C', 'Graph D', '', '4', 'Active', NULL),
(191, 16, 'If the spot price of Tyranus, Corp’s stock declines to $6.00 per share just prior to the expiration date, Tyranus would most likely:', 'Exercise the option and realize a $2 per share gain.', 'Allow the option to expire worthless.', 'Lock in their hedging gains using a forward contract.', 'Purchase the underlying stock and incur a $2 per share net loss.', '', '4', 'Active', NULL),
(192, 16, 'Which of the following actions could Tyranus, Corp. take to protect themselves from potential losses resulting from their short put options?', 'Enter into a long put option with a higher strike price.', 'Purchase shares of their common stock in the market.', 'Sell a put option to a different counterparty with the same strike price.', 'Issue additional shares of their common stock.', '', '1', 'Active', NULL),
(193, 16, 'Rancor, Inc. has sold a call option tied to the stock price of Jabba, Corp. Rancor has also purchased shares of Jabba Corp.’s stock to protect them from losses on the option contract that would result from sharp increases in the stock price. This hedging strategy is generally referred to as:', 'A straddle.', 'A covered call.', 'A combination.', 'A bull spread.', '', '2', 'Active', NULL),
(194, 21, '<p><strong>The following business cycle graph depicts changes in GDP growth over a period of several years.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img src="https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/ltDcdOQgFpo6I3tPcBrhq_USz6umgkJ1ZBAvpLiD0i14OlkzY60r8nJVs8IXzb-O9vQStcNY-e2ZVLxp0DSFh2kURumx9LU3Rqnc0sjOFdeCT5YrFmTCcpoZsBmnxn8Au2QL52KJq9jPS4kfUg" style="height:210px; width:329px" /></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Which of the following phases of the business cycle is most likely occurring at <u>Point A</u> on the graph above?</strong></p>', 'Peak.', 'Recession.', 'Trough.', 'Expansion.', '', '2', 'Active', ''),
(195, 21, '<p><strong>Which of the following phases of the business cycle is most likely occurring at <u>Point B</u>&nbsp;on the graph above?</strong></p>', 'Peak.', 'Recession.', 'Trough.', 'Expansion.', '', '3', 'Active', ''),
(196, 21, '<p><strong>Which of the following phases of the business cycle is most likely occurring at <u>Point C</u> on the graph above?</strong></p>', 'Peak.', 'Recession.', 'Trough.', 'Expansion.', '', '4', 'Active', ''),
(197, 21, '<p><strong>Which of the following phases of the business cycle is most likely occurring at <u>Point D</u> on the graph above?</strong></p>', 'Peak.', 'Recession.', 'Trough.', 'Expansion.', '', '1', 'Active', ''),
(198, 21, '<p><strong>An economist at Lannister Corp. has prepared a presentation on the state of the economy for the company&rsquo;s Board of Directors. He notes in his presentation that after several years of growth, the economy has entered a &lsquo;slowdown&rsquo; period. An increase in which of the following economic measures would most likely support this conclusion?</strong></p>', 'Durable good exports.', 'Gross domestic product.', 'Excess business inventories.', 'Home prices.', '', '3', 'Active', ''),
(199, 21, '<p><strong>An investor is monitoring various economic indicators as a means for making investment decisions. Economic indicators are most useful for predicting changes in which of the following?</strong></p>', 'Tax rates.', 'Accounting rules.', 'The business cycle.', 'Government regulation.', '', '3', 'Active', ''),
(200, 0, '<p><strong>An economist at Stark Corp. is reviewing historical data on three economic indicators (Indicators A, B and C) in order to assess their usefulness in predicting future recessions. Her research focused on the following factors: (1) the correlation that past movements in these indicators had with changes in the economy and (2) whether these movements occurred before, after, or concurrently with the changes in the economy. Based on her research, she noted the following:</strong></p>', 'Leading and procyclical.', 'Lagging and procyclical.', 'Coincident and acyclical.', 'Leading and countercyclical.', '', '', 'Active', ''),
(201, 21, '<p><strong>An economist at Stark Corp. is reviewing historical data on three economic indicators (Indicators A, B and C) in order to assess their usefulness in predicting future recessions. Her research focused on the following factors: (1) the correlation that past movements in these indicators had with changes in the economy and (2) whether these movements occurred before, after, or concurrently with the changes in the economy. Based on her research, she noted the following:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/2OaMqtB9sPYtu1MgsWVc2mWdepzaU6YGBq_wpJy5J-798iZ_mbXdkhJG6L279qx9440rbx5agHKAotVxmf9zr4lLNyvSZNA83EqoY-tukSyvnwQCiHM7A2OyE8v-aqh22dhz7ua6" style="height:131px; width:380px" /><strong> </strong></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Based on the information above, <u>Indicator A</u> would most likely be classified as:</strong></p>', 'Leading and procyclical.', 'Lagging and procyclical.', 'Coincident and acyclical.', 'Leading and countercyclical.', '', '4', 'Active', ''),
(202, 21, '<p><strong>Based on the information above, <u>Indicator B</u> would most likely be classified as:</strong></p>', 'Lagging and countercyclical.', 'Coincident and procyclical.', 'Lagging and procyclical.', 'Leading and countercyclical.', '', '2', 'Active', ''),
(203, 21, '<p><strong>Based on the information above, Indicator C would most likely be classified as:</strong></p>', 'Lagging and procyclical.', 'Leading and acyclical.', 'Lagging and countercyclical.', 'Coincident and countercyclical.', '', '1', 'Active', ''),
(204, 21, '<p><strong>Sansa is an investor that is monitoring economic indicators by reviewing a measure that provides her with a prediction of the economic future based on the combination several separate forecasts that have been made using varying methodologies. This type of measure would most likely referred to as:</strong></p>', 'A consensus forecast.', 'A coincident index.', 'An economic calendar.', 'A production report.', '', '1', 'Active', ''),
(205, 21, '<p><strong>Which of the following transactions would most likely take place in a financial market?</strong></p>', 'Company A receives a 5 year loan from a bank.', 'Company B purchases land using excess cash.', 'Company C transfers machinery to one of its subsidiaries.', 'Company D consolidates its finance company subsidiary for financial reporting purposes.', '', '1', 'Active', ''),
(206, 21, '<p><strong>Jaime, Tyrion, and Cersei have all recently purchased financial instruments from Casterly Rock Bank. Jaime has purchased a 180-day certificate of deposit that earns a 4% annualized fixed rate of interest. Tyrion has purchased 300 shares of common stock through Casterly Rock&rsquo;s online trading website. Cersei has purchased a 5-year floating rate bond through Casterly Rock&rsquo;s investment bank; the bond was issued by Tyrell Corp and underwritten by Casterly Rock.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Jaime&rsquo;s certificate of deposit is an example of which of the following?</strong></p>', 'A mutual fund.', 'An equity security.', 'A money market instrument.', 'A commodity.', '', '3', 'Active', ''),
(207, 21, '<p><strong>Which of the following benefits will Tyrion most likely realize through his investment of common stock?</strong></p>', 'A short maturity period.', 'Guaranteed price appreciation.', 'A fixed rate of interest.', 'Dividend income.', '', '4', 'Active', ''),
(208, 21, '<p><strong>Cersei&rsquo;s bond is closely associated with which of the following financial markets?</strong></p>', 'Primary money market.', 'Secondary money market.', 'Primary capital market.', 'Secondary capital market.', '', '3', 'Active', ''),
(209, 21, '<p><strong>Braavos Bank wishes to invest some of its excess funds in a highly liquid, short-term debt instrument. Which of the following financial markets would Braavos most likely purchase such an instrument?</strong></p>', 'The capital market.', 'The bond market.', 'The stock market.', 'The money market.', '', '4', 'Active', ''),
(210, 21, '<p><strong>Which of the following transactions involving a U.S.-based company would most likely occur in the foreign exchange markets? </strong></p>', 'Company A purchases stock of a foreign-owned company on the NYSE.', 'Company B converts U.S. dollars into euros.', 'Company C issues debt securities in a foreign market.', 'Company D purchases a bond with a fixed interest rate.', '', '2', 'Active', ''),
(211, 21, '<p><strong>Which of the following transactions would most likely occur in the commodities market?</strong></p>', 'Company A purchases Japanese yen from a foreign bank.', 'Company B sells long-term debt securities to a third party.', 'Company C issues commercial paper to investors.', 'Company D purchases an oil futures contract from an exchange.', '', '4', 'Active', ''),
(212, 21, '<p><strong>Stannis has received a $10,000 loan from ABC Bank with a five year payment term. Interest on Stannis&rsquo;s loan is calculated on a simple basis. Davos has purchased an $8,000 savings bond from XYZ Bank (the issuer) with a four-year term and a 5% stated interest rate. The interest on Davos&rsquo; bond is calculated annually based on both the outstanding principal and previously accrued interest. Principal repayment and accumulated interest associated with the bond are remitted to Ben upon maturity.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>If Stannis makes semi-annual interest payments of $300 under the terms of the loan, then the stated interest rate equals:</strong></p>', '0%.', '3%.', '6%.', '15%.', '', '3', 'Active', ''),
(213, 21, '<p><strong>Which of the following best describes the form of interest that Davos is earning on his XYZ Bank bond investment?</strong></p>', 'Compound.', 'Variable.', 'Simple.', 'Floating.', '', '1', 'Active', ''),
(214, 21, '<p><strong>If the yield-to-maturity on Davos&rsquo; bond investment equals 4%, the instrument was most likely purchased:</strong></p>', 'At a premium.', 'In the money markets.', 'At a discount.', 'In a secondary market.', '', '1', 'Active', ''),
(215, 21, '<p><strong>Catelyn (a financial analyst) is currently observing the bond markets in hopes of purchasing of a new bond investment. Bond A is currently being offered with a 1-year term-to-maturity; Bond B is currently being offered with a 5-year term-to-maturity; Bond C is currently being offered with a 10-year term-to-maturity. &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Which of the following interest rate observations would be indicative of a flat yield curve in the bond market?</strong></p>', 'Bond A pays 8% interest; Bond B pays 7% interest; Bond C pays 6% interest.', 'Bond A pays 4% interest; Bond B pays 8% interest; Bond C pays 9% interest.', 'Bond A pays 6% interest; Bond B pays 6% interest; Bond C pays 6% interest.', 'Bond A pays 6% interest; Bond B pays 7% interest; Bond C pays 8% interest.', '', '3', 'Active', ''),
(216, 21, '<p><strong>Catelyn observes that bonds with identical risk, liquidity and tax characteristics have different interest rates because their remaining maturities are different. The concept that can best explain this observation is referred to as the:</strong></p>', 'Equilibrium interest rate.', 'Risk structure of interest rates.', 'Default risk premium.', 'Term structure of interest rates.', '', '4', 'Active', ''),
(217, 21, '<p><strong>Tywin is attempting to calculate GDP by summing all outflows of money spent on final goods and services for the previous fiscal year (20X5). He has compiled the following sector outflows data:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><img src="https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/ItIDQxVriblI6YvPC9a24wRCf1MqPzhZT6wmAbV94ePzh3we6-96sQVS8TBRsAcHzAmhgbYlP0bVd6T5hFkkMhQ8vcSR1y2lWpJvc51g0xVoFkPe1CL4grrHJmGreUlEeBROQu9T" style="height:199px; width:509px" />The method utilized by Tywin for measuring GDP would most likely be identified as the _________ approach. </strong></p>', 'Surplus.', 'Expenditure.', 'Deficit.', 'Income.', '', '2', 'Active', ''),
(218, 21, '<p><strong>Based on the data provided above, the amount of consumption outflows (C) that should be included in Tywin&rsquo;s calculation of GDP equals: </strong></p>', '$6.5 trillion.', '$7.5 trillion.', '$8.5 trillion.', '$10.5 trillion.', '', '4', 'Active', ''),
