(494, 14, '<p><strong>Which best describes the recommended practice for receiving invoices by e-mail?</strong></p>', 'e-mailed invoices should be refused', 'e-mailed invoices should be discouraged', 'e-mailed invoices should all be sent to one e-mail address', 'e-mailed invoices should be accepted wherever the supplier wants to send them', '', '3', 'Active', ''),
(495, 14, '<p><strong>What should be done with invoices that do not contain either a PO number or the name of the purchaser?</strong></p>', 'They should be paid', 'AP should figure out who made the purchase', 'They should be sent to the controller', 'They should be returned to the supplier requesting the missing information', '', '4', 'Active', ''),
(496, 14, '<p><strong>When developing a coding standard, which of the following principles apply?</strong></p>', 'Every organization should do it the same way', 'Every processor within the organization should do it the same way', 'Every processor should be able to develop their own standard', 'Every processor should use the standard used at their former company', '', '2', 'Active', ''),
(497, 14, '<p><strong>When it comes to short-paying an invoice, what is the best policy regarding communicating the reason for the short payment?</strong></p>', 'Don’t worry about it; there’s no need to let the vendor know', 'Let the vendor try and figure out the reason themselves', 'Put what you can on the remittance advice and let the vendor figure out the rest', 'Find a way to easily share the information with the vendor', '', '4', 'Active', ''),
