(600, 43, '<p><strong>Which of the following best completes the sentence?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>A member who departs from Rulings in similar circumstances ________.</strong></p>', 'will be requested to justify the departure.', 'is still ethical since these are not principles, but only rulings.', 'is not considered ethical, but because of the circumstances does not have to justify it.', 'is still ethical because rulings are only guidelines.', '', '1', 'Active', ''),
(601, 44, '<p><strong>A member would NOT be considered independent if he/she provides Investment Advisory services, AND:</strong></p>', 'Recommends the allocation of funds that a client should invest in various asset classes.', 'Reviews the manner in which a client''s portfolio is being managed by investment account managers.', 'Reviews the transactions for the client made by the member.', 'Performs recordkeeping and reporting of client''s portfolio balances.', '', '3', 'Active', ''),
(602, 44, '<p><strong>Which of the following statements is NOT correct?</strong></p>', 'The Principles provide the framework within which the Rules operate.', 'The Rules govern the conduct of the members.', 'The bylaws of the AICPA require adherence to both Rules and those standards emanating from the Rules.', 'The Rules provide the framework within which the Principles operate.', '', '4', 'Active', ''),
(603, 44, '<p><strong>The Rules of Conduct do NOT apply to:</strong></p>', 'All services performed by a CPA unless specifically stated in the Code.', 'All audits and other attestation activities.', 'Services performed in public accounting.', 'The client being audited.', '', '4', 'Active', ''),
(604, 44, '<p><strong>Which of the following best completes the sentence? </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The effective date of the AICPA pronouncements of Interpretations and Rulings is:</strong></p>', 'The last day of the month in which it is published in The Journal of Accountancy.', 'The end of the grace period received, which is a year.', 'The date the pronouncement is issued.', 'One Year from date of issuance.', '', '1', 'Active', ''),
(605, 44, '<p><strong>Which of the following statements is FALSE?</strong></p>', 'A client is a person or entity that engages a member to perform professional services.', 'A firm is a partnership that is engaged in the practice of public accounting.', 'Interpretations of rules of conduct are guidelines for specific situations issued by the division of professional ethics concerning the application of the rules of conduct.', 'Professional services include only attest functions performed by a member while holding out as a CPA.', '', '4', 'Active', ''),
(606, 44, '<p><strong>The concept of a Code of Ethics is:</strong></p>', 'To force upright behavior by professionals.', 'To provide rigorous guidelines for behavior.', 'Needed for keeping professionals moral.', 'Needed for keeping clients moral.', '', '2', 'Active', ''),
(607, 44, '<p><strong>The trust function could NOT be fulfilled by which of the following:</strong></p>', 'A group with very high standards of ethical conduct.', 'The trust that exists when “savers” give over their savings to “users.”', 'Our society’s normal moral standards.', 'The CPA in our society with the high standards of ethical conduct of the profession.', '', '3', 'Active', ''),
(608, 44, '<p><strong>When is a member required to disclose to a client that a commission will be received under the &ldquo;Commissions and Referral Fees Rule&rdquo;? </strong></p>', 'Never, the Commissions and Referral Fees Rule does not require a member to disclose that a commission will be received.', 'At the end of the engagement, once the work has been completed.', 'Only if the client asks the member during the period of the engagement.', 'At the time referral is being made so that the client can decide whether to act on the recommendation.', '', '4', 'Active', ''),
(609, 44, '<p><strong>Which of the following is the BEST answer concerning the actions a CPA should follow concerning Independence?</strong></p>', 'It may be needed for some to keep them upright.', 'The true professional will be willing to stay upright by adhering to the set of ethical principles and standards adopted by his or her profession.', 'The spirit of the Code of Ethics is more important than just trying to stay in bounds.', 'The Code of Ethics should represent the very minimum standard of conduct.', '', '2', 'Active', ''),
(610, 44, '<p><strong>It is permitted by the Code of Ethics that advertising may be: </strong></p>', 'Misleading.', 'False.', 'Outright in presenting fees associated with services.', 'Mostly factual in its presentation of the firm.', '', '3', 'Active', ''),
(611, 44, '<p><strong>Auditing Standards are set by which of the following:</strong></p>', 'State Ethics Statutes.', 'Pronouncements of the AICPA and other similar agencies.', 'The State Technical Standards Rules.', 'The State Behavioral Standards Rules.', '', '2', 'Active', ''),
(612, 44, '<p><strong>A person shall be deemed to be engaged in the practice of public accountancy if he or she ___</strong></p>', 'As an employee keeps books and makes trial balances as a part of a bookkeeping service.', 'Prepares or signs, as the tax preparer, tax returns for clients.', 'Is an employee of a certified public accountant who does not issue reports over their name.', 'Is an attorney at law, and a CPA, in connection with their practice of law.', '', '2', 'Active', ''),
(613, 44, '<p><strong>A contingent fee is one that will be received for services:</strong></p>', 'That may be performed on a specific project.', 'The extent of which depends on the results of the initial work.', 'The amount of which is dependent upon the results of that service in determining a specific finding.', 'That may be performed on a research project of unknown length.', '', '3', 'Active', ''),
(614, 44, '<p><strong>Complete the following sentence: Lawyers represent clients in various capacities, EXCEPT as:</strong></p>', 'A zealous independent protector of society.', 'An advisor.', 'An evaluator.', 'A negotiator.', '', '1', 'Active', ''),
(615, 44, '<p><strong>Which of the following statements is true?</strong></p>', 'Internal auditors may accept token gifts.', 'CPAs may accept token gifts.', 'Internal auditors may accept any gift.', 'CPAs may not accept any gifts.', '', '2', 'Active', ''),
(616, 44, '<p><strong>A person engaged in the practice of public accountancy is prohibited from performing services for a commission for all of the following EXCEPT:</strong></p>', 'An officer of a client.', 'A director of a client.', 'A compilation client in which the CPA is not independent and states so.', 'A client-sponsored retirement plan.', '', '3', 'Active', ''),
(617, 44, '<p><strong>A member of the AICPA is responsible to which of the following groups?</strong></p>', 'The state society to which the member belongs.', 'The appropriate state board of accountancy.', 'The AICPA ethics division.', 'All of the above.', '', '4', 'Active', ''),
(618, 44, '<p><strong>A CPA borrows $12,000 from a client for the purchase of a car and makes a $4,000 down payment. The rate and terms are the same as those that other car buyers in a similar situation would receive. A loan from the client to the CPA would:</strong></p>', 'Produce a permitted loan.', 'Affect independence.', 'Not produce a permitted loan since the CPA would be independent.', 'Not produce a permitted loan since the CPA would not be independent.', '', '1', 'Active', ''),
(619, 44, '<p><strong>Which of the following is NOT an exception to client confidentiality rules:</strong></p>', 'A member must comply with a valid subpoena of a court.', 'A member must allow review by an appropriate AICPA or state CPA society.', 'A member may initiate a complaint or respond to one of a recognized investigative body.', 'A client’s name is considered non-confidential information and therefore may be revealed.', '', '4', 'Active', ''),
(620, 44, '<p><strong>Which of the following best completes the sentence?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>A member who departs from Rulings in similar circumstances ________.</strong></p>', 'will be requested to justify the departure.', 'is still ethical since these are not principles, but only rulings.', 'is not considered ethical, but because of the circumstances does not have to justify it.', 'is still ethical because rulings are only guidelines.', '', '1', 'Active', ''),
(621, 35, '<p><strong>Orsillo Inc. presents their manufacturing equipment on the balance sheet at the price paid for it at the time of acquisition. In addition, Orsillo reduces this basis each period to reflect customary wear and tear on the equipment. This measurement basis is known as:</strong></p>', 'Fair value.', 'Periodic expense.', 'Market value.', 'Historical cost.', '', '4', 'Active', ''),
(622, 35, '<p><strong>Remy Corp. presents their investment securities on the balance sheet at the price that would be received to sell them in an orderly transaction between market participants. This measurement basis is known as:</strong></p>', 'Fair value.', 'Depreciation.', 'Periodic expense.', 'Historical cost.', '', '1', 'Active', ''),
(623, 35, '<p><strong>A writer for a financial journal is drafting an article that discusses the primary criticisms of the historical cost and fair value accounting methods. Which of the following statements would most accurately describes one of these criticisms?</strong></p>', 'Fair value accounting places too much focus on allocating the cost of an asset over its useful life on the Income Statement.', 'Fair value accounting is strictly based on historical records of the transactions.', 'Historical cost accounting ignores fundamental economic principles that affect the true value of any asset, such as inflation and currency fluctuations.', 'Historical cost accounting focuses on presenting an asset on the Balance Sheet at its current market value.', '', '3', 'Active', ''),
(624, 35, '<p><strong>Maroney Electric holds numerous types of assets that it accounts for at fair value, including various financial instruments and physical assets. Which of the following statements most accurately summarizes FASB&rsquo;s recommended approach for valuing these assets? </strong></p>', 'Maroney should apply one definition of fair value to all their assets.', 'Maroney should apply a unique definition of fair value to each major asset class.', 'Maroney should apply separate definitions of fair value to their financial and physical assets.', 'Maroney should apply one definition of fair value to all of their physical assets, and a distinct definition to each class of financial instruments.', '', '1', 'Active', ''),
(625, 35, '<p><strong>ABC Corp. is a new company that will be adopting the concepts of ASC 820 in their annual financial statements this year. Which of the following will most likely change as a result of this adoption?</strong></p>', 'The number of asset classes accounted for at fair value.', 'The amount of fair value-related disclosures.', 'The cost basis of ABC’s investment portfolio.', 'The accounting for ABC’s stock compensation plan.', '', '2', 'Active', ''),
(626, 35, '<p><strong>Which of the following hypothetical transactions would provide the best estimate of an investment&rsquo;s &ldquo;fair value&rdquo; under the guidance of ASC 820? </strong></p>', 'The investment is sold in a “forced sale”.', 'The investment is liquidated as part of bankruptcy proceedings.', 'The investment is sold in an orderly transaction between market participants.', 'The investment is sold to a related party.', '', '3', 'Active', ''),
(627, 35, '<p><strong>For the following 3 questions, please refer to this information:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Youkilis Corp. is preparing the monthly fair value accounting entries for their investment securities portfolio. The securities are currently trading in an active market. Youkilis is considered an active participant in the securities market.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Under the guidance of ASC 820, &nbsp;the &lsquo;exit price&rsquo; of the Youkilis investments is: </strong></p>', 'The price that would be received to sell the securities.', 'The price paid to acquire the securities.', 'Conceptually the same as ‘entry price’ for financial instruments.', 'The required measurement basis for all assets & liabilities.', '', '1', 'Active', ''),
(628, 35, '<p><strong>Under the guidance of ASC 820, &nbsp;the &lsquo;entry price&rsquo; is: </strong></p>', 'The price that would be received to sell the securities.', 'The price paid to acquire the securities.', 'Conceptually the same as ‘exit price’ for financial instruments.', 'The required measurement basis for all assets & liabilities.', '', '2', 'Active', ''),
(629, 35, '<p><strong>The fair value measurement that Youkilis estimates must assume that the securities being valued are exchanged in: </strong></p>', 'A forced transaction.', 'An illiquid market.', 'An orderly transaction.', 'A distressed sale.', '', '3', 'Active', ''),
(630, 35, '<p><strong>For the following 4 questions, please refer to this information:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Companies A and B both actively purchase and sell widgets; both companies apply ASC 820 when measuring them at fair value on their respective balance sheets. The principal market for widgets is the retail market, where they trade for $100 per unit. Widgets are also available in a secondary market, where they trade for $150 per unit. Company A actively trades widgets in both markets, while Company B only has access to the retail market. </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Under the requirements of ASC 820, the per-unit fair value of Company A&rsquo;s widgets would equal $______, while the per-unit fair value of Company B&rsquo;s widgets would equal $______.</strong></p>', '$150; $100.', '$100; $150.', '$100; $100.', '$150; $150.', '', '3', 'Active', ''),
(631, 35, '<p><strong>Which of the following widget valuation methodologies is the most consistent with the requirements of ASC 820? &nbsp;</strong></p>', 'Company A uses an entity-specific measurement basis.', 'Company B uses a historical-cost measurement basis.', 'Company A uses a government-mandated measurement basis.', 'Company B uses a market-based measurement basis.', '', '4', 'Active', ''),
(632, 35, '<p><strong>The determination of the principal (or most advantageous) market for widgets is made from the perspective of: </strong></p>', 'The most active participants in the widget market.', 'Participants in the wholesale market for widgets.', 'Participants in the secondary market for widgets.', 'The reporting entity.', '', '4', 'Active', ''),
(633, 35, '<p><strong>Companies C &amp; D would most likely be considered participants in the widget market if they were: </strong></p>', 'Motivated (but not forced) to purchase and sell widgets.', 'Subsidiaries of large widget-producing companies.', 'Unable to transact widgets due to regulatory constraints.', 'Unfamiliar with widgets.', '', '1', 'Active', ''),
(634, 35, '<p><strong>Bay Ltd. values their rental properties (including the land and the apartment buildings) using the in-use valuation premise under ASC 820. In-use assets such as Bay&rsquo;s provide maximum value when:</strong></p>', 'They are also the highest and best use of the asset.', 'The price is determined based on the lowest bid.', 'The price is the lowest for a group of assets.', 'The asset is a financial asset.', '', '1', 'Active', ''),
(635, 35, '<p><strong>Which of the following items most likely represents the &lsquo;unit of account&rsquo; for the corresponding asset presented?</strong></p>', 'Last-in, first-out (Inventory).', 'An individual debt security (Investments).', 'Allowance for doubtful accounts (Accounts Receivable).', 'Historical cost (Fixed Assets).', '', '2', 'Active', ''),
(636, 35, '<p><strong>Which of the following scenarios represents an explicit requirement of ASC 820?</strong></p>', 'Company A measures all assets on the balance sheet at fair value.', 'Company B strictly relies on internal assumptions when determining the fair value of their investments portfolio.', 'Company C depreciates their fixed assets using a straight-line methodology.', 'Company D applies the guidance found in the fair value framework when estimating the fair value of their financial contracts.', '', '4', 'Active', ''),
(637, 35, '<p><strong>Company A uses prices published on the New York Stock Exchange to determine the fair value of its equities portfolio. Under ASC 820, this valuation technique would be considered consistent with the: </strong></p>', 'Market approach.', 'Income approach.', 'Cost approach.', 'Equity approach.', '', '1', 'Active', ''),
(638, 35, '<p><strong>Company B uses a discounted cash flow model to determine the fair value of its subsidiary. Under ASC 820, this valuation technique would be considered consistent with the: </strong></p>', 'Market approach.', 'Income approach.', 'Cost approach.', 'Fixed income approach.', '', '2', 'Active', ''),
(639, 35, '<p><strong>Company C values its software asset on the Balance Sheet by estimating the amount that would currently be required to construct a substitute software asset of comparable utility (considering functional, technological and economic obsolescence). Under ASC 820, this valuation technique would be considered consistent with the: </strong></p>', 'Market approach.', 'Income approach.', 'Cost approach.', 'Technology approach.', '', '3', 'Active', ''),
(640, 35, '<p><strong>Wally Corp. utilizes observable foreign exchange rates when measuring the fair value of its international corporate bond investments. A foreign exchange rates are considered an example of _________ under ASC 820. </strong></p>', 'An entity-specific measurement.', 'A depreciation method.', 'A market participant.', 'A valuation input.', '', '4', 'Active', ''),
(641, 35, '<p><strong>For the following 3 questions, please refer to this information:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Lowrie Inc. is currently developing a methodology to estimate the fair value of their financial assets portfolio. This portfolio contains shares of ABC Corp. common stock, several mortgage-backed securities and some credit derivatives. &nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Lowrie uses quoted prices from the New York Stock Exchange to determine the fair value of their ABC Corp. common stock. Such observable inputs are generally considered _______ under ASC 820: &nbsp;</strong></p>', 'Level 1 inputs.', 'Level 2 inputs.', 'Level 3 inputs.', 'Prohibited.', '', '1', 'Active', ''),
(642, 35, '<p><strong>Unobservable assumptions that Lowrie Inc. uses when valuing its mortgage-backed securities are generally considered _______ under ASC 820. &nbsp;</strong></p>', 'Level 1 inputs', 'Level 2 inputs', 'Level 3 inputs', 'Prohibited', '', '3', 'Active', ''),
(643, 35, '<p><strong>Published interest rate observations that are used to value Lowe&rsquo;s mortgage-backed securities under the income approach are considered _______ under ASC 820.</strong></p>', 'Level 1 inputs', 'Level 2 inputs', 'Level 3 inputs', 'Prohibited', '', '2', 'Active', ''),
(644, 35, '<p><strong>Which of the following policies is the most compliant with the fair value hierarchy outlined in ASC 820?</strong></p>', 'Company A gives the highest priority to historical cost information.', 'Company B gives the highest priority to internally-developed valuation data.', 'Company C gives the highest priority to quoted prices in active markets.', 'Company D gives the highest priority to valuations supported by management.', '', '3', 'Active', ''),
(645, 35, '<p><strong>Which of the following practices complies with ASC 820&rsquo;s expanded disclosure requirements for fair value measurements?</strong></p>', 'Company A discloses their investing and hedging activities.', 'Company B discloses the valuation techniques used to measure fair value.', 'Company C discloses their amortization methods.', 'Company D discloses the extent to which they measures assets and liabilities at amortized cost.', '', '2', 'Active', ''),
(646, 35, '<p><strong>Wally Corp. owns several assets that the company accounts for at fair value. Under ASC 820, the company&rsquo;s fair value disclosure requirements will vary depending on whether these assets are:</strong></p>', 'Debt instruments or equity instruments.', 'Amortized or depreciated.', 'Taxable or non-taxable investments.', 'Measured on a recurring or nonrecurring basis.', '', '4', 'Active', ''),
(647, 35, '<p><strong>Which of the following describes an auditor&rsquo;s responsibilities related to the presentation and disclosure of fair value measurements under SAS 101?</strong></p>', 'Auditor A obtains sufficient audit evidence to provide reasonable assurance that the fair value measurements and disclosures are in conformity with GAAP.', 'Auditor B establishes an accounting and financial reporting process for determining fair value measurements.', 'Auditor C calculates the fair value measurements and disclosures included in the client’s financial statements.', 'Auditor D assigns Level 1, 2 or 3 classifications to the various fair value measurements included in the client’s financial statements.', '', '1', 'Active', ''),
(648, 35, '<p><strong>Which of the following describes management&rsquo;s responsibilities related to the presentation and disclosure of fair value measurements under SAS 101?</strong></p>', 'Company A’s management obtains sufficient audit evidence to provide reasonable assurance that the fair value measurements and disclosures are in conformity with GAAP.', 'Company B’s management establishes an accounting and financial reporting process for determining fair value measurements.', 'Company C’s management tests their significant assumptions and the underlying data used in their valuation model.', 'Company D’s management performs substantive tests of their fair value disclosures.', '', '2', 'Active', ''),
(649, 35, '<p><strong>Mayo Corp. owns two types of Level 3 assets that it accounts for at fair value: financial assets that are measured at fair value on a recurring basis and intangible assets that are measured at fair value on a nonrecurring basis. Mayo is preparing a reconciliation of beginning and ending balances for fair value measurements that use significant unobservable inputs for their annual report. This reconciliation is ________ for their financial assets and ________ for their intangible assets.</strong></p>', 'Not required; not required.', 'Not required; required.', 'Required; not required.', 'Required; required.', '', '3', 'Active', ''),
(650, 35, '<p><strong>Which of the following describes substantive tests that would most likely be performed for fair value measurements under SAS 101?</strong></p>', 'Auditor A develops independent fair value estimates for corroborative purposes.', 'Auditor B requires the client to measure its assets or liabilities using valuation models under all circumstances.', 'Auditor C prepares the fair value measurements and related disclosures included in the client’s financial statements.', 'Auditor D disregards subsequent events and transactions if engagement time constraints exist.', '', '1', 'Active', ''),
(651, 35, '<p><strong>Which of the following accounting practices would likely involve the use of significant assumptions on the part of management? </strong></p>', 'Client A values its common stock holdings using quoted market prices.', 'Client B accounts for its equipment using the historical cost method.', 'Client C reconciles cash balances on a daily basis.', 'Client D values its businesses using internally-developed cash flow projections.', '', '4', 'Active', '');
INSERT INTO `course_exam_questions` (`ques_id`, `course_id`, `ques_title`, `ques_ans_1`, `ques_ans_2`, `ques_ans_3`, `ques_ans_4`, `ques_ans_5`, `correct_ans_id`, `ques_status`, `question_image`) VALUES
(652, 35, '<p><strong>Which of the following accounting practices related the fair value option is permitted by ASC 825-10? </strong></p>', 'Bank A elected the fair value option for a loan with an embedded derivative.', 'Bank B revoked its use of the fair value option for its financial asset.', 'Bank C elected the fair value option for its deposit liabilities.', 'Bank D elected the fair value option for a loan commitment that it wrote five years ago.', '', '1', 'Active', ''),
(653, 35, '<p><strong>Moss Corp. has issued a 10-year corporate bond (i.e. a financial liability) that contains an embedded derivative that is not &lsquo;clearly and closely related&rsquo; to the host instrument. Under GAAP, Moss: </strong></p>', 'May elect the fair value option account for the entire instrument at fair value.', 'Must measure the embedded derivative at historical cost on its balance sheet.', 'May ignore the embedded derivative for financial reporting purposes.', 'Is prohibited from accounting for the entire instrument at fair value.', '', '1', 'Active', ''),
(654, 35, '<p><strong>For the following 3 questions, please refer to this information: </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Wilfork Corp. wishes to elect the fair value option (&ldquo;FVO&rdquo;) for many of its assets and liabilities in the coming year to eliminate several accounting inconsistencies that exist.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Under ASC 825-10, Wilfork would most likely be permitted to elect the fair value option for its:</strong></p>', 'Lease liabilities.', 'Convertible debt securities.', 'Written loan commitments.', 'Employee stock options.', '', '3', 'Active', ''),
(655, 35, '<p><strong>Under ASC 825-10, Wilfork would most likely be prohibited from electing the fair value option for its:</strong></p>', 'Consolidated interests in variable interest entities.', 'Own debt.', 'Written loan commitments.', 'Hybrid securities.', '', '1', 'Active', ''),
(656, 35, '<p><strong>When recording the accounting entries to reflect fair value gains on its FVO assets, Wilfork would debit the balance sheet account associated with these assets and credit:</strong></p>', 'Other comprehensive income.', 'Net income.', 'Equity.', 'Retained earnings.', '', '2', 'Active', ''),
(657, 35, '<p><strong>Which of the following observations are indicative of an active market under the guidance of ASC 820 (as amended by FSP FAS 157-4)?</strong></p>', 'Company A receives valuations from multiple sources that differ significantly.', 'Company B sees unusually low transaction volume occurring in the market.', 'Company C receives price quotations that are based on current information.', 'Company D observes low correlations between indexes and asset values.', '', '3', 'Active', ''),
(658, 35, '<p><strong>Watson Inc. exclusively relies on quoted market prices when valuing its assets. Which of the following is true regarding the use of such inputs when estimating fair value?</strong></p>', 'Quotes prices must never be adjusted when estimating fair value.', 'Quotes prices may not be determinative of fair value if the asset is traded in an inactive market.', 'Quotes prices are classified as Level 3 inputs in the fair value hierarchy.', 'Quotes prices are normally estimated using significant judgment and complex valuation models.', '', '2', 'Active', ''),
(659, 35, '<p><strong>Which of the following approaches is the most consistent with the concepts of proper valuation outlined in the CAQ white paper &ldquo;Measurements of Fair Value in Illiquid (or Less Liquid Markets)?</strong></p>', 'Company A estimates the price that would be received in an inactive market.', 'Company B estimates the price that would be received in an active market.', 'Company C estimates the price that would be received in current market conditions.', 'Company D estimates the price that would be received in a forced liquidation.', '', '3', 'Active', ''),
(660, 35, '<p><strong>A newspaper writer has developed a story outlining the credit crisis and recession of 2007-2009. Which of the following excerpts would most likely be included in this article to accurately describe the&nbsp;role that fair value accounting played in the crisis?</strong></p>', 'The anti-cyclical nature of fair value accounting prevented investors from realizing even larger losses during the crisis.', 'ASC 820 placed insufficient emphasis on the use of quoted market prices, thus exacerbating the crisis.', 'Accounting literature on fair value created a downward bias on asset valuations during the crisis.', 'The lack of guidance on the definition of “fair value” resulted in fraudulent financial reporting.', '', '3', 'Active', ''),
(661, 46, '<p><strong>The following two states have not enacted sales and use tax legislation:</strong></p>', 'Texas and Oregon.', 'Alaska and Hawaii.', 'New Hampshire and Oregon.', 'Delaware and Nevada.', '', '3', 'Active', ''),
(662, 46, '<p><strong>The following statement applies to the states that have enacted sales and/or use tax programs:</strong></p>', 'Most states have enacted both sales and use tax legislation, but a few have restricted their programs to sales taxes only.', 'In states with sales and use tax programs, the taxing agencies must pursue sellers for unpaid sales tax and purchasers for unpaid use tax.', 'When sellers are required to collect another state’s tax, it’s generally sales tax that’s involved.', 'States are constitutionally prohibited from imposing sales tax on transactions that occur outside their borders.', '', '4', 'Active', ''),
(663, 46, '<p><strong>The following is an integral concept/characteristic pertaining to sales and use tax nexus:</strong></p>', 'Nexus can be defined as the threshold of connection that would require a business to register with a state and collect that state’s sales and use taxes.', 'Each state has the final authority to establish its own rules for determining when a company is doing business within its boundaries for purposes of asserting sales and use tax nexus.', 'The primary federal criteria for sales and use tax nexus proceed from two clauses of the U.S. Constitution: the Dormant Taxation Clause and the Commerce Clause.', 'As the case law has evolved, the Commerce Clause has become less important as a basis for determining sales and use tax nexus.', '', '1', 'Active', ''),
(664, 46, '<p><strong>In <em>Quill Corporation v. North Dakota</em>, the U.S Supreme Court did <u>not</u> resolve the following issue:</strong></p>', 'Whether regular or systematic solicitation of a consumer market in the state (defined as making three or more solicitations within a 12 month period, by any means) would support a finding of nexus as mandated by a state statute.', 'Whether the growth of the mail-order business subsequent to the Court’s previous decisions, coupled with advances in computer technology that could ease the burden of sales and use tax compliance, rendered the prior case law obsolete.', 'The establishment of concrete criteria for identifying “substantial nexus.”', 'The relative importance of the Commerce Clause of the U.S. Constitution in the determination of nexus.', '', '3', 'Active', ''),
(665, 46, '<p><strong>The following level of physical presence in a state would be regarded as <em>de minimus</em> (i.e., too insignificant to rise to the level of &ldquo;substantial nexus&rdquo;).</strong></p>', 'A magazine publisher maintains a small in-state news bureau which compiles news stories for the magazine.  One of the employees at the news bureau also solicits advertising for placement in the magazine.  The publisher has no other physical presence in the state.', 'A mail-order company advertises through catalogs and mailings and makes all of its deliveries by common carrier.  Its only in-state property is CDs containing purchasing software that it provided to three of its customers to facilitate the customers’ ability to make purchases from the company.', 'A company’s sole physical presence in a state consists of periodic deliveries of its merchandise to in-state customers in the company’s vehicles.', 'An out-of-state company rents caps and gowns to graduating students in the state through local teacher/representatives.', '', '2', 'Active', ''),
(666, 46, '<p><strong>Which of the following circumstances would not create nexus for the out-of-state party?</strong></p>', 'An out-of-state lessor of office equipment leases a copier to an in-state business under a three-year contract.  The lessor ships the copier by common carrier to the lessee, who engages a local repair person to set the unit up.', 'An out-of-state software vendor licenses the use of its computer programs to in-state customers.  The vendor transmits the software to its customers over the Internet and provides no tangible personal property.  The customers’ state excludes electronically transmitted software from its definition of tangible personal property subject to the tax.', 'An out-of-state company leases a remote computer server from an in-state lessor.', 'An out-of-state company licenses software to in-state customers via Internet downloads.   The customers’ state regards prewritten and custom software as tangible personal property subject to the tax, whether the transfers are made through physical media or by direct electronic download.', '', '2', 'Active', ''),
(667, 46, '<p><strong>In which of the following situations would visits into the state by one or more representatives of a remote vendor not result in an assertion of nexus? &nbsp;(Assume the vendor has no other physical presence in the state.)</strong></p>', 'Arizona: A non-employee representative spends four days in the state providing technical assistance to the vendor’s customers.', 'New York: Employees of the vendor’s wholesale division visit potential customers in the state 12 times during a 3-year period but do not accept orders.', 'Florida: The vendor’s only physical contacts with the state are an annual visit by an employee to one customer (where no orders are taken), and shipments to the vendor’s Florida customers from a third-party manufacturer’s in-state warehouse.', 'Illinois: A couple of times a year, the vendor engages local Illinois contractors to provide construction related services (installation of materials sold by the vendor) in the state.  The vendor does not send its own employees into the state.', '', '3', 'Active', ''),
(668, 46, '<p><strong>A company with no other in-state presence exhibits its product at a 5-day trade show. &nbsp;It does not solicit sales or take orders at the show but attends solely to show the merits of its product in the hope of promoting remote sales in the future. &nbsp;Based only on this activity, the state requires the company to take out a sales tax permit and collect, report and remit the tax on all sales shipped to in-state customers for the 12 months following the date of the trade show. &nbsp;Which of the following states would be likely to take this position?</strong></p>', 'Texas.', 'New York.', 'Maine.', 'California.', '', '1', 'Active', ''),
(669, 46, '<p><strong>The following state statutes, cases, and rulings appear to be consistent with the leading U.S. Supreme Court case, <em>Quill Corporation v. North Dakota:</em></strong></p>', 'Under Florida law, a corporate seller is automatically engaged in business in the state if the seller is eligible to file a consolidated tax return with a Florida affiliate having nexus with the state.', 'An Ohio statute asserts nexus for an out-of-state seller with an in-state franchisee (separate legal entity) that uses a trade name of the seller, or an out-of-state seller that is a member of an affiliated group if the group includes at least one member with “substantial nexus” to the state.', 'The Indiana Department of Revenue held that an out-of-state LLC had nexus based on the presence of a related corporation inside the state.  The decision did not articulate why the state considered the corporation to be related.', 'The Massachusetts Department of Revenue held that nexus would not be created for an out-of-state company that opened in-state store affiliates that were separate legal entities selling similar products under related company names.  The out-of-state company accepted returns under a “repurchase” policy that was available for items sold by its in-state affiliates as well as for items purchased from unrelated competitors.  The affiliates would use common gift certificates, but the in-state entities would not promote sales for the out-of-state company.  The Department concluded that the in-state stores would not be creating or maintaining a market for the out-of-state company because its market had already been established, and the out-of-state affiliate’s sales would actually drop significantly after opening stores in the state.', '', '4', 'Active', ''),
(670, 46, '<p><strong>In order for a state to successfully assert click-through nexus against an out-of-state seller, the following conditions must be present:</strong></p>', 'The out-of-state company’s sales resulting from in-state sources must exceed a specific dollar amount for the preceding year.', 'A business within the state must provide a link on its website to the website of an out-of-state seller that enables the customers of the in-state business to buy from the out-of-state seller.  The details of the arrangement must establish that the in-state business is acting as an agent of the outside seller.', 'The number of clicks on the in-state company’s link must exceed an annual minimum threshold.', 'The state’s law must stipulate that the out-of-state seller will not be permitted to rebut the presumption of nexus.', '', '2', 'Active', ''),
(671, 46, '<p><strong>Typical (although not universal) parameters for click-through nexus include the following: the out-of-state company&rsquo;s annual sales resulting from in-state sources must exceed a certain dollar amount; the out-of state company must compensate the in-state sources through commissions or other methods based on sales; and the in-state sources must &ldquo;solicit&rdquo; (as defined by each individual state) on behalf of the out-of-state company in a manner that can be significantly associated with the latter&rsquo;s ability to establish or maintain an in-state market. &nbsp;The following states do not apply these parameters:</strong></p>', 'New York and Arkansas.', 'California and Connecticut.', 'Colorado and Hawaii.', 'Kansas and Minnesota.', '', '3', 'Active', ''),
(672, 46, '<p><strong>In most states, the following activity generally will result in an assertion of nexus even though the taxpayer has no other presence in the state:</strong></p>', 'The taxpayer has contracted to do business with a state agency.  (The state has not enacted legislation or issued regulations specifically requiring entities doing business with the state to obtain sales tax permits.)', 'The taxpayer has obtained a certificate of authority to transact business in the state.', 'The taxpayer has voluntarily registered to collect the state’s sales and use tax.', 'The taxpayer has incorporated within the state.', '', '3', 'Active', ''),
(673, 46, '<p><strong>When a company receives a nexus questionnaire from a state in which it has no physical presence, the company should proceed as follows:</strong></p>', 'Engage an in-state litigation specialist to interact with the state.', 'Assign the response to the person responsible for filing the company’s sales and use tax returns for states where the company has nexus.', 'Since the company has no physical presence in the state, it need not respond to the questionnaire.', 'Engage a sales and use tax specialist who is familiar with the inquiring state’s nexus criteria to prepare a response.', '', '4', 'Active', ''),
(674, 46, '<p><strong>Company A has sold products to residents of its home state for two decades and has collected, reported, and remitted the state&rsquo;s sales tax for the entire time. &nbsp;Seven years ago, the company began soliciting sales in a neighboring state and selling and shipping its products to that state&rsquo;s residents. &nbsp;Company A did not register with the neighboring state&rsquo;s taxing agency because its officers believed that it lacked a physical presence therein and therefore was not required to do so. &nbsp;The company&rsquo;s tax director recently learned that Company A has, in fact, had nexus to the neighboring state since it began selling to the state&rsquo;s residents. &nbsp;Company A&rsquo;s next step should be:</strong></p>', 'Assuming the neighboring state is a participant in the Streamlined Sales Tax Project, the company should apply for full membership in the Project immediately.', 'Assuming the neighboring state is a participant in the Multistate Tax Commission’s Voluntary Disclosure Program, the company should fill out and submit the Commission’s voluntary disclosure application for that state only.', 'The company should register with the neighboring state, since registration will limit the state’s ability to tax the prior sales to its applicable statute of limitations (normally three or four years).', 'The company should register with the neighboring state, report and pay tax on all of its prior sales to the state’s residents, and request relief of penalties and interest.', '', '2', 'Active', ''),
(675, 46, '<p><strong>The Marketplace Fairness Act is:</strong></p>', 'A provision of the Streamlined Sales Tax Agreement that forces remote sellers to collect sales and use taxes on sales into member states, whether or not the sellers have nexus to those states.', 'A recently enacted federal law that will enable any state to collect sales and use tax from out-of-state vendors that lack nexus.', 'Proposed legislation that would enable states belonging to the Multistate Tax Commission to collect sales and use tax from out-of-state vendors that lack nexus.', 'Proposed legislation intended to permit states to collect sales and use tax from out-of-state vendors that lack nexus.', '', '4', 'Active', ''),
(676, 45, '<p><strong>Your client is using QuickBooks Enterprise 16.0 and while you are working on-site you want to use the new Batch Delete/Void feature. Which of the following scenarios would be required? </strong></p>', 'Log into the file as the Admin user and unlock the Accountant ToolBox.', 'Log into the file as the External Accountant user and unlock the Accountant ToolBox.', 'Log into the file as the Admin or External Accountant user.', 'All of the above.', '', '3', 'Active', ''),
(677, 45, '<p><strong>While helping a client who has been using QuickBooks for many years, you notice that there are hundreds of invoices waiting to be emailed. What can your client do to remove all of the invoices from the Send Forms queue?</strong></p>', 'Remove the checkmark in the Email Later box on each Create Invoice window.', 'From the File menu, select Remove Send Forms, and select Remove Forms.', 'From the File menu, select Send Forms, and select Remove Forms.', 'From the Company menu, select Send Forms, and select Remove Forms.', '', '3', 'Active', ''),
(678, 45, '<p><strong>In this course, you learned about a new Auto Copy address feature released with QuickBooks Desktop 2016. What forms does the Auto Copy feature work with? </strong></p>', 'Create Invoices.', 'Create Purchase Orders.', 'Create Estimates.', 'Enter Bills.', '', '2', 'Active', ''),
(679, 45, '<p><strong>QuickBooks E-Invoicing (sending an invoice for payment by email) is available for use with which version(s) of QuickBooks Desktop? </strong></p>', 'QuickBooks Pro.', 'QuickBooks Enterprise.', 'QuickBooks Premier and Accountant.', 'QuickBooks Pro, Premier, Accountant and Enterprise.', '', '4', 'Active', ''),
(680, 45, '<p><strong>When upgrading QuickBooks Desktop from a year&#39;s version prior to QuickBooks Desktop 2016, which statement best describes the process? </strong></p>', 'The upgrade process has been simplified.', 'The upgrade process remains the same as previous year’s upgrade experience.', 'The upgrade process suggests that a backup be made prior to upgrading the file.', 'The upgrade process has been removed as a requirement to change a file from one year to another year.', '', '1', 'Active', ''),
(681, 48, '<p><strong>A member would NOT be considered independent if he/she provides Investment Advisory services, AND:</strong></p>', 'Recommends the allocation of funds that a client should invest in various asset classes.', 'Reviews the manner in which a client''s portfolio is being managed by investment account managers.', 'Reviews the transactions for the client made by the member.', 'Performs record-keeping and reporting of client''s portfolio balances.', '', '3', 'Active', ''),
(682, 48, '<p><strong>Which of the following statements is <u>NOT </u>correct?</strong></p>', 'The Principles provide the framework within which the Rules operate.', 'The Rules govern the conduct of the members.', 'The bylaws of the AICPA require adherence to both Rules and those standards emanating from the Rules.', 'The Rules provide the framework within which the Principles operate.', '', '4', 'Active', ''),
(683, 48, '<p><strong>The Rules of Conduct do NOT apply to:</strong></p>', 'All services performed by a CPA unless specifically stated in the Code.', 'All audits and other attestation activities.', 'Services performed in public accounting.', 'The client being audited.', '', '4', 'Active', ''),
(684, 48, '<p><strong>Which of the following best completes the sentence? </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The effective date of the AICPA pronouncements of Interpretations and Rulings is:</strong></p>', 'The last day of the month in which it is published in The Journal of Accountancy.', 'The end of the grace period received, which is a year.', 'The date the pronouncement is issued.', 'One Year from date of issuance.', '', '1', 'Active', ''),
(685, 48, '<p><strong>Which of the following statements is <u>FALSE</u>?</strong></p>', 'A client is a person or entity that engages a member to perform professional services.', 'A firm is a partnership that is engaged in the practice of public accounting.', 'Interpretations of rules of conduct are guidelines for specific situations issued by the division of professional ethics concerning the application of the rules of conduct.', 'Professional services include only attest functions performed by a member while holding out as a CPA.', '', '4', 'Active', ''),
(686, 48, '<p><strong>The concept of a Code of Ethics is:</strong></p>', 'To force upright behavior by professionals.', 'To provide rigorous guidelines for behavior.', 'Needed for keeping professionals moral.', 'Needed for keeping clients moral.', '', '2', 'Active', ''),
(687, 48, '<p><strong>The trust function could NOT be fulfilled by which of the following:</strong></p>', 'A group with very high standards of ethical conduct.', 'The trust that exists when “savers” give over their savings to “users.”', 'Society’s normal moral standards.', 'The CPA in our society with the high standards of ethical conduct of the profession.', '', '3', 'Active', ''),
(688, 48, '<p><strong>When is a member required to disclose to a client that a commission will be received under the &ldquo;Commissions and Referral Fees Rule&rdquo;? </strong></p>', 'Never, the Commissions and Referral Fees Rule does not require a member to disclose that a commission will be received.', 'At the end of the engagement, once the work has been completed.', 'Only if the client asks the member during the period of the engagement.', 'At the time referral is being made so that the client can decide whether to act on the recommendation.', '', '4', 'Active', ''),
(689, 48, '<p><strong>Which of the following is the <u>BEST</u> answer concerning the actions a CPA should follow concerning Independence?</strong></p>', 'It may be needed for some to keep them upright.', 'The true professional will be willing to stay upright by adhering to the set of ethical principles and standards adopted by his or her profession.', 'The spirit of the Code of Ethics is more important than just trying to stay in bounds.', 'The Code of Ethics should represent the very minimum standard of conduct.', '', '2', 'Active', ''),
(690, 48, '<p><strong>Which of the following is Correct? &nbsp;Every licensee engaged in the practice of public accountancy shall provide notice to the licensee&#39;s clients of the fact that the licensee is licensed by the Board of Accountancy by:</strong></p>', 'Posting a notice in a public area of the premises where the licensee provides the licensed services, in at least 12-point type, that states the named licensee is licensed by the Board of Accountancy.', 'A written notice that is electronically transmitted which is reasonably calculated to be received by the licensee''s clients.', 'Both A&B', 'Neither A&B', '', '2', 'Active', ''),
(691, 48, '<p><strong>&nbsp;It is permitted by the Code of Ethics that advertising may be: </strong></p>', 'Misleading.', 'False.', 'Outright in presenting fees associated with services.', 'Mostly factual in its presentation of the firm.', '', '3', 'Active', ''),
(692, 48, '<p><strong>Auditing Standards are set by which of the following:</strong></p>', 'State Ethics Statutes.', 'Pronouncements of the AICPA and other similar agencies.', 'The State Technical Standards Rules.', 'The State Behavioral Standards Rules.', '', '2', 'Active', ''),
(693, 48, '<p><strong>A person shall be deemed to be engaged in the practice of public accountancy if he or she ___:</strong></p>', 'As an employee keeps books and makes trial balances as a part of a bookkeeping service.', 'Prepares or signs, as the tax preparer, tax returns for clients.', 'Is an employee of a certified public accountant who does not issue reports over their name.', 'Is an attorney at law, and a CPA, in connection with their practice of law.', '', '2', 'Active', ''),
(694, 48, '<p><strong>A contingent fee is one that will be received for services:</strong></p>', 'That may be performed on a specific project.', 'The extent of which depends on the results of the initial work.', 'The amount of which is dependent upon the results of that service in determining a specific finding.', 'That may be performed on a research project of unknown length.', '', '3', 'Active', ''),
